y AI-assisted technologies** and **may contain occasional formatting or logic errors**. Please report any issues you encounter so I can improve the experience._\n\n\n::: \n\n\n___\n\n\n### üìò Part 1 (until Midterm)\n\n| Module | Chapter | \n|:-------:|:--------:|\n| 3 | ch11 | \n\n\n___\n\n**Answer the following questions based on the discussions in class.**\n\n<script>\n  const SLIDE_ID = \"module3_p3num\";\n</script>\n\n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q1.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Expected Return, Variance, and Standard Deviation of a Portfolio\n\n\n\nWhat is the **expected return** of a portfolio that invests **22.84**% in Asset&nbsp;1 (expected return = **13.62**%) and the remaining **77.16**% in Asset&nbsp;2 (expected return = **6.74**%   )?\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q1a\"><strong>1. What is the expected return of the portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <!-- Only two decimal places in the answer -->\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q1a\" name=\"module3_num_q1a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=8.31 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q1a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Expected return = w‚ÇÅ√ór‚ÇÅ + w‚ÇÇ√ór‚ÇÇ = **8.31**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\nWhat is the **variance** of the portfolio above, given correlation **0.68**, standard deviation of Asset&nbsp;1 = **30.17**% and of Asset&nbsp;2 = **19.02**%?\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q1b\"><strong>2. What is the variance of the portfolio (in squared %)?</strong></label>\n  <!-- Only two decimal places in the answer -->\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q1b\" name=\"module3_num_q1b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=4 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q1b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Variance = w‚ÇÅ¬≤œÉ‚ÇÅ¬≤ + w‚ÇÇ¬≤œÉ‚ÇÇ¬≤ + 2w‚ÇÅw‚ÇÇœÅœÉ‚ÇÅœÉ‚ÇÇ = **4**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\nWhat is the **standard deviation** of the portfolio above?\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q1c\"><strong>3. What is the standard deviation of the portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <!-- Only two decimal places in the answer -->\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q1c\" name=\"module3_num_q1c\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=19.99 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q1c\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Standard deviation = ‚àö(variance) = **19.99**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q2.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Portfolio Weight Calculation for Multiple Stocks\n\n\n\nSuppose you purchase **232** shares of Company&nbsp;A at \\$**55.55** per share, **149** shares of Company&nbsp;B at \\$**38.62** per share, and **26** shares of Company&nbsp;C at \\$**51.42** per share.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q2a\"><strong>1. What is the weight on Company&nbsp;A in your portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q2a\" name=\"module3_num_q2a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=64.51 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q2a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Weight on Company A = value_A / total_value √ó 100 = **64.51**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q3.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Portfolio Variance and Standard Deviation Calculation\n\n\n\nYou invest **23.16%** of your funds in Asset A (volatility = **14.97%**) and **76.84%** in Asset B (volatility = **18.62%**). The correlation between the two assets is **0.61**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n<label for=\"module3_num_q3a\"><strong>1. What is the variance of your portfolio (in squared %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q3a\" name=\"module3_num_q3a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=277.78 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q3a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Portfolio variance = w¬≤√ósd‚ÇÅ¬≤ + (1‚àíw)¬≤√ósd‚ÇÇ¬≤ + 2√ów√ó(1‚àíw)√ósd‚ÇÅ√ósd‚ÇÇ√óœÅ = **277.78**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n<label for=\"module3_num_q3b\"><strong>2. What is the standard deviation of your portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q3b\" name=\"module3_num_q3b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=16.67 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q3b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Portfolio standard deviation = ‚àö(variance) = **16.67**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q4.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Calculating Beta Using Covariance and Market Variance\n\n\n\nGiven that the covariance between a stock and the market is **4.47** and the variance of the market is **5.2**,\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n<label for=\"module3_num_q4a\"><strong>1. What is the beta of the stock?</strong></label>\n  <!-- Two decimal places for the beta -->\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q4a\" name=\"module3_num_q4a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=0.86 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q4a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Beta = Cov(asset, market) / Var(market) = **0.86**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q5.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Risk Premium and Sharpe Ratio Calculation\n\n\n\nAn investment has an expected return of **7.32%**, a risk‚Äëfree rate of **2.18%**, and a volatility (standard deviation) of **16.25%**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n<label for=\"module3_num_q5a\"><strong>1. What is the risk premium (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <!-- Two decimal places for the risk premium -->\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q5a\" name=\"module3_num_q5a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=5.14 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q5a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Risk premium = expected return ‚àí risk‚Äëfree rate = **5.14**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n<label for=\"module3_num_q5b\"><strong>2. What is the Sharpe ratio (return per unit of risk)?</strong></label>\n  <!-- Two decimal places for the Sharpe ratio -->\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q5b\" name=\"module3_num_q5b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=0.32 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q5b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Sharpe ratio = risk premium / volatility = **0.32**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q6.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Combining Risky Asset and Risk‚ÄëFree Rate\n\n\n\nYou invest **40.29%** of your funds in a risky portfolio (expected return = **5.69%**, volatility = **12.4%**) and the remainder **59.71%** in the risk‚Äëfree asset (rate = **3.88%**).\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q6a\"><strong>1. What is the expected return of your portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q6a\" name=\"module3_num_q6a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=4.61 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q6a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Expected return = w√óret_risky + (1‚àíw)√óRf = **4.61**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q6b\"><strong>2. What is the standard deviation of your portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q6b\" name=\"module3_num_q6b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=5 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q6b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Since the risk‚Äëfree asset has zero volatility, the portfolio‚Äôs volatility equals w√óœÉ_risky = **5**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q7.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Beta of a Three‚ÄëAsset Portfolio\n\n\n\nYou hold a portfolio composed of three assets with betas **0.53**, **1.09**, and **0.08**, invested in proportions **9.37%**, **76.54%**, and **14.09%**, respectively.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q7a\"><strong>1. What is the beta of the portfolio?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q7a\" name=\"module3_num_q7a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=0.89 data-tolerance=\"0.1\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q7a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Portfolio beta = w‚ÇÅ√óŒ≤‚ÇÅ + w‚ÇÇ√óŒ≤‚ÇÇ + w‚ÇÉ√óŒ≤‚ÇÉ = **0.89**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q8.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Expected Return via CAPM\n\n\n\nThe risk‚Äëfree rate is **2.98%**, the market risk premium is **6.13%**, and the beta of the investment is **1.08**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q8a\"><strong>1. What is the expected return of the investment according to the CAPM (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q8a\" name=\"module3_num_q8a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=9.59 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q8a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Expected return = Rf + Œ≤ √ó (market risk premium) = **9.59**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q9.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Variance and Volatility of a Three‚ÄëAsset Portfolio\n\n\n\nYou invest **54.96%**, **32.37%**, and **12.67%** of your funds in three assets with volatilities **14.07%**, **23.99%**, and **14.44%**, respectively. The pairwise correlations are œÅ‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ**0**, œÅ‚ÇÅ‚ÇÉ‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ**-0.07**, and œÅ‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ‚ÄØ=‚ÄØ**-0.09**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q9a\"><strong>1. What is the variance of the portfolio?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q9a\" name=\"module3_num_q9a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=118.99 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q9a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Variance = Œ£w·µ¢¬≤œÉ·µ¢¬≤ + 2Œ£ w·µ¢w‚±ºœÉ·µ¢œÉ‚±ºœÅ·µ¢‚±º = **118.99**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q9b\"><strong>2. What is the standard deviation of the portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q9b\" name=\"module3_num_q9b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=10.91 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q9b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Standard deviation = ‚àö(variance) = **10.91**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q10.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Risk‚ÄëFree Combination and Sharpe Ratio\n\n\n\nYou build a portfolio by combining the risk‚Äëfree asset (rate = **3.98%**) with a tangent portfolio (expected return = **11.8%**, volatility = **17.64%**) using a weight of **135.54%** in the tangent portfolio (weights greater than 100% imply leverage).\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q10a\"><strong>1. What is the expected return of your combined portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q10a\" name=\"module3_num_q10a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=14.58 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q10a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Expected return = w√óret_tan + (1‚àíw)√óRf = **14.58**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q10b\"><strong>2. What is the standard deviation of your combined portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q10b\" name=\"module3_num_q10b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=23.92 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q10b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Standard deviation = |w|√óœÉ_tan = **23.92**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q10c\"><strong>3. What is the Sharpe ratio of your combined portfolio?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q10c\" name=\"module3_num_q10c\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=0.44 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q10c\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Sharpe ratio = risk premium / volatility = **0.44**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n::: {.webex-box}\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;\">Q11.</div>\n  <div style=\"flex: 1;\">\n## Sharpe Calculation\n\n\n\nAn investment has an expected return of **7.02%**, a risk‚Äëfree rate of **2.15%**, and a volatility (standard deviation) of **11.44%**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module2_num_q11a\"><strong>1. What is the risk premium (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module2_num_q11a\" name=\"module2_num_q11a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=4.87 data-tolerance=\"0.1\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module2_num_q11a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Risk premium = expected return ‚àí risk‚Äëfree rate = **4.87**%.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module2_num_q11b\"><strong>2. What is the Sharpe ratio?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module2_num_q11b\" name=\"module2_num_q11b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=0.426 data-tolerance=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module2_num_q11b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n‚úÖ Sharpe ratio = risk premium / volatility = **0.426**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n::: \n\n\n\n\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<script>\n// Fun√ß√£o auxiliar para verificar e definir o status de uma quest√£o.\nfunction checkAnswerAndSetStatus(questionId, userAnswer, correctAnswer, feedbackDivId, tolerance = 0) {\n  const feedbackDiv = document.getElementById(feedbackDivId);\n  if (!feedbackDiv) return;\n\n  let isCorrect = false;\n\n  // Trata respostas num√©ricas com toler√¢ncia\n if (typeof correctAnswer === 'number' && typeof userAnswer === 'number' && !isNaN(userAnswer)) {\n    const lowerBound = correctAnswer - tolerance;\n    const upperBound = correctAnswer + tolerance;\n    isCorrect = (userAnswer >= lowerBound && userAnswer <= upperBound);\n  } else if (typeof userAnswer === 'string') {\n    // Para respostas de texto (T/F, M√∫ltipla Escolha)\n    isCorrect = (userAnswer.trim().toUpperCase() === correctAnswer.toUpperCase());\n  }\n  // Adicione outras l√≥gicas de compara√ß√£o aqui se necess√°rio (ex: arrays para m√∫ltiplos checkboxes)\n\n  if (isCorrect) {\n    feedbackDiv.dataset.status = \"correct\";\n  } else {\n    feedbackDiv.dataset.status = \"incorrect\";\n  }\n  feedbackDiv.style.display = \"none\"; // Mant√©m o feedback oculto\n}\n\n// Fun√ß√£o para obter a resposta de um grupo de radio buttons\nfunction getSelectedRadioValue(name) {\n    const radios = document.querySelectorAll(`input[type=\"radio\"][name=\"${name}\"]:checked`);\n    if (radios.length > 0) {\n        return radios[0].value;\n    }\n    return ''; // Retorna string vazia se nada for selecionado\n}\n\nfunction toggleFeedback() {\n  const questionBlocks = document.querySelectorAll('.question-block');\n  const feedbacks = document.querySelectorAll('.feedback');\n  const scoreDiv = document.getElementById('score-summary');\n  const toggleButton = document.getElementById('toggle-feedback-btn');\n\n  let showing = feedbacks.length > 0 && feedbacks[0].style.display === 'block';\n\n  if (showing) {\n    // Esconder feedback\n    feedbacks.forEach(f => {\n      f.style.display = 'none';\n      f.style.color = 'black'; // Reseta a cor ao esconder\n    });\n    scoreDiv.textContent = '';\n    toggleButton.textContent = 'Show Feedback';\n  } else {\n    // Mostrar feedback\n    let correctCount = 0;\n    let totalQuestions = 0;\n\n    questionBlocks.forEach(block => {\n      totalQuestions++;\n      const textInput = block.querySelector('input[type=\"text\"]');\n      const numberInput = block.querySelector('input[type=\"number\"]'); // Novo: input num√©rico\n      const form = block.querySelector('form');\n\n      let questionId, userAnswer, correctAnswer, tolerance = 0;\n      let feedbackDivId;\n\n      if (textInput && textInput.dataset.correctAnswer) {\n        // Quest√£o de texto (T/F)\n        questionId = textInput.id;\n        userAnswer = textInput.value;\n        correctAnswer = textInput.dataset.correctAnswer;\n      } else if (numberInput && numberInput.dataset.correctAnswer) {\n        // Quest√£o num√©rica\n        questionId = numberInput.id;\n        // Converte para n√∫mero. Se n√£o for um n√∫mero v√°lido, NaN.\n        userAnswer = parseFloat(numberInput.value);\n        correctAnswer = parseFloat(numberInput.dataset.correctAnswer);\n        if (numberInput.dataset.tolerance) {\n          tolerance = parseFloat(numberInput.dataset.tolerance);\n        }\n        // Se a resposta do usu√°rio n√£o for um n√∫mero v√°lido, trate como incorreta\n        if (isNaN(userAnswer)) {\n             userAnswer = null; // Mant√©m como valor num√©rico inv√°lido\n        }\n      } else if (form && form.querySelector('input[type=\"radio\"]') && form.dataset.correctAnswer) {\n        // Quest√£o de m√∫ltipla escolha (radio)\n        questionId = form.querySelector('input[type=\"radio\"]').name;\n        userAnswer = getSelectedRadioValue(questionId);\n        correctAnswer = form.dataset.correctAnswer;\n      } else {\n        // Se n√£o for um tipo de quest√£o reconhecido ou n√£o tem resposta correta\n        totalQuestions--; // N√£o conta esta quest√£o no total se n√£o puder ser avaliada\n        return; // Pula para a pr√≥xima quest√£o\n      }\n\n      feedbackDivId = 'feedback-' + questionId;\n      const feedbackDiv = document.getElementById(feedbackDivId);\n\n      if (feedbackDiv) { // Apenas processa se h√° um feedback div\n        checkAnswerAndSetStatus(questionId, userAnswer, correctAnswer, feedbackDivId, tolerance);\n\n        // Agora, exibe e colore o feedback ap√≥s a verifica√ß√£o\n        if (feedbackDiv.dataset.status === 'correct') {\n          feedbackDiv.style.color = 'green';\n          correctCount++;\n        } else if (feedbackDiv.dataset.status === 'incorrect') {\n          feedbackDiv.style.color = 'red';\n        } else {\n          feedbackDiv.style.color = 'black'; // Se n√£o foi respondida ou n√£o tem status\n        }\n        feedbackDiv.style.display = 'block'; // Exibe o feedback\n      }\n    });\n\n    scoreDiv.textContent = `‚úÖ  You answered ${correctCount} out of  ${totalQuestions}  correctly.`;\n    toggleButton.textContent = 'Hide Feedback';\n  }\n}\n</script>\n\n<button id=\"toggle-feedback-btn\" onclick=\"toggleFeedback()\"\n  style=\"background-color:#007BFF; color:white; padding:8px 16px; border:none; border-radius:5px; cursor:pointer;\">\n  Show Feedback\n</button>\n<div id=\"score-summary\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; font-weight: bold;\"></div>\n\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;\">\n  <a href=\"/teaching/financial_strategy/\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-lg\">\n    üîô\n  </a>\n</div>\n",
